column4: CORRECTED-Microsoft workers demand it drop $480 mln U.S. Army contract
column5: SAN FRANCISCO  Feb 22 Several Microsoft Corp employees on Friday demanded that the company cancel a $480 million hardware contract with the U.S. Army and stop developing "any and all weapons technologies."

column4: Exxon  Microsoft strike cloud computing agreement for U.S. shale
column5: Exxon Mobil Corp and Microsoft Corp have agreed to use cloud technology in the U.S. oil producer's shale operations  they said on Friday  helping to boost profitability in the nation's largest shale field.

column4: Tesla rolls out Model 3 in China ahead of schedule in sales push
column5: BEIJING/SHANGHAI Tesla Inc has started delivering Model 3 cars in China slightly ahead of schedule  as it looks to revive its sales that have been hit hard by Sino-U.S. trade tensions.

column4: UPDATE 2-Tesla rolls out Model 3 in China ahead of schedule in sales push
column5: * Tesla had expected to start Model 3 China deliveries in March

column4: Tesla starts Model 3 delivery in China earlier than expected
column5: BEIJING  Feb 22 Tesla Inc on Friday said it had started delivering Model 3 cars in China  slightly ahead of schedule.

column4: Consumer Reports yanks recommendation for Tesla's Model 3  citing reliability
column5: DETROIT Consumer Reports on Thursday pulled a recommendation for Tesla Inc's Model 3  citing reliability problems  and the influential U.S. magazine turned up the pressure on other automakers to include crash-avoiding automatic braking as standard equipment.

column4: Intel says its 5G modem chips will not appear in phones until 2020
column5: Intel Corp executives said on Friday its 5G modem chips will not appear in mobile phones until 2020  raising the possibility its biggest customer  Apple Inc  will be more than a year behind rivals in delivering a device that uses the faster networks.
